=== Proving decoupling, not just "it flew" (the actual point of Phase 4) ===

ros2 topic info /sentinelflight/proposed_setpoint -v
  Publisher count: 1  -> sentinelflight_mission_manager
  Subscription count: 2 -> sentinelflight_safety_gate, sentinelflight_telemetry_logger
  (offboard_controller does NOT subscribe here — it never sees a raw,
   unvalidated proposal, exactly as docs/architecture.md specifies)

ros2 topic info /sentinelflight/safe_setpoint -v
  Publisher count: 1  -> sentinelflight_safety_gate (the only node that ever
  decides what reaches PX4)
  Subscription count: 2 -> sentinelflight_offboard_controller, sentinelflight_telemetry_logger

ros2 node info /sentinelflight_offboard_controller
  Subscribers: /fmu/out/vehicle_local_position_v1, /sentinelflight/safe_setpoint
  Publishers:  /fmu/in/offboard_control_mode, /fmu/in/trajectory_setpoint,
               /fmu/in/vehicle_command
  (only node in the graph publishing to any /fmu/in/* topic, confirming
   "the ONLY node that talks to PX4 directly")

ros2 topic echo /sentinelflight/safety_event --once
  timestamp: 1784830911.7352014
  status: 0        (APPROVED)
  state: 0         (NORMAL)
  reason: OK
  ai_confidence: 0.949999988079071
  failsafe_active: false

ros2 topic echo /sentinelflight/proposed_setpoint --once
  x: 0.0
  y: 0.0
  z: 5.0
  vx: 0.0
  vy: 0.0
  vz: 0.0
  (MissionManager reached SEARCH and is holding at TAKEOFF_ALTITUDE_M, as
  expected with no perception publisher yet — see docs/roadmap.md "Phase 4
  notes")

=== PX4 vehicle_status / vehicle_local_position samples during the flight ===

arming_state: 2   (ARMING_STATE_ARMED)
nav_state: 14     (NAVIGATION_STATE_OFFBOARD)
z: -4.99          (holding at the 5m target altitude; PX4 NED, negative = up)

... (hold, then AUTO_LAND handoff) ...

arming_state: 1   (ARMING_STATE_STANDBY — disarmed)
nav_state: 14
z: -0.007         (back at ground level)

=== Safety gate ===

Ran scripts/analyze_logs.py against the full arm-through-disarm window
(docs/evidence/phase4_mission_sample.csv, 9619 rows @ 10 Hz):

  Rows: 9619
  Altitude: min=-0.02m max=5.00m avg=0.11m
  AI confidence: min=0.95 max=0.95 avg=0.95
  Safety status breakdown:
    APPROVED: 9619

Zero rejections across the full cycle — safety_gate_node evaluated every
tick end-to-end against live PX4 state, now running as its own process,
receiving proposals only over /sentinelflight/proposed_setpoint and
publishing decisions only over /sentinelflight/safe_setpoint and
/sentinelflight/safety_event.

=== Known limitation (carried over from Phase 2, observed again here) ===

offboard_controller keeps publishing the OffboardControlMode heartbeat
after commanding AUTO_LAND, which still appears to delay PX4's
disarm-after-landing logic. In this run it took roughly 16 minutes
(1784829389 -> ~1784830349) to disarm on its own — longer than the "few
minutes" observed in Phase 3 — but it did disarm without intervention.
Still tracked as follow-up work (stop the heartbeat once AUTO_LAND is
commanded), not fixed in Phase 4.
